Episodes.description: The Simpsons go back to New York City so that Bart can find his old girlfriend Mary Spuckler. Meanwhile, Lisa and Marge spend the trip trying to take in New York culture on the cheap.
Episodes.title: Moonshine River

Episodes.description: A black hole threatens to swallow Springfield, Homer tries to find the source of paranormal activity, and a "Back to the Future" parody in which Bart keeps Marge from marrying Homer.
Episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XXIII

Episodes.description: Marge decides that she wants another baby, but Homer doesn't want one. Meanwhile, Bart tries to figure out where Lisa is secretly going after school.
Episodes.title: Adventures in Baby-Getting

Episodes.description: Homer invests Lisa's college fund on an online poker site. Meanwhile Abe disappears from the Springfield Retirement Castle.
Episodes.title: Gone Abie Gone

Episodes.description: Fat Tony has to serve jury duty, and his clerk, Dan, must run the mafia while he's gone. Meanwhile, Lisa considers making a disgusting change to her diet.
Episodes.title: Penny-Wiseguys

Episodes.description: Homer becomes addicted to his new tablet computer. But when it is destroyed Homer becomes despondent, until he finds and provides hope for Springfield in the most unlikely place.
Episodes.title: A Tree Grows in Springfield

Episodes.description: Homer befriends a hipster and invites his family to move in next door. However, their friendship soon sours as Springfield is transformed into a haven for "coolness."
Episodes.title: The Day the Earth Stood Cool

Episodes.description: When Homer shows no remorse over almost losing Santa's Little Helper, Grandpa tells everyone the story of Homer's childhood dog.
Episodes.title: To Cur With Love

Episodes.description: Homer joins the "Springfield Preppers," an off-the-grid survivalist group whose leader has set up a top-secret retreat outside of town to prepare for the end of the world.
Episodes.title: Homer Goes to Prep School

Episodes.description: The fate of Springfield Elementary rests on Bart and his test scores, and Homer finds way to make money with his own parking meter.
Episodes.title: A Test Before Trying

Episodes.description: Homer and Marge find the perfect young couple and ask them to be the guardians for the kids in case something happens to them.
Episodes.title: Changing of the Guardian

Episodes.description: Mary Spuckler returns to Springfield and begins a relationship with Bart. However, Bart treats her with disrespect.
Episodes.title: Love is a Many Splintered Thing

Episodes.description: Bart poses Millhouse as his father so that they can do adult activities, and Homer becomes skilled at finding lost objects thanks to Highlights magazine.
Episodes.title: Hardly Kirk-ing

Episodes.description: Homer's obsession with the TV show "Storage Battles" leads the family to discover Grampa's past identity as "Gorgeous Godfrey," the most feared, villainous man in pro-wrestling history
Episodes.title: Gorgeous Grampa

Episodes.description: Ned gets fed up with Homer and punches him in the eye, and Lisa is a bullying victim from her new substitute teacher.
Episodes.title: Black-eyed Please

Episodes.description: When Bart is accused of a prank he says he didn't commit, Lisa is forced to defend him in youth court, with former attorney general Janet Reno serving as judge.
Episodes.title: Dark Knight Court

Episodes.description: Homer contemplates his next move after getting in the doghouse with Marge, while Millhouse's new Stanley Kowalski-inspired persona makes him suddenly attractive to Lisa.
Episodes.title: What Animated Women Want

Episodes.description: ringfield gets a bedbug scare, the new assistant pastor at church appoints Homer as a deacon, and Marge loses her wedding dress.
Episodes.title: Pulpit Friction

Episodes.description: A new makeover could put Moe in a position to make big money, Bart fails at his job of taking care of Grandpa, and Lisa fights the shameless exploitation of Bleeding Gums Murphy's likeness.
Episodes.title: Whiskey Business

Episodes.description: Bart takes piano lessons from a cute Russian girl, Marge tries to teach the girl's father how to drive, and Homer loses the last of his hair.
Episodes.title: The Fabulous Faker Boy

Episodes.description: Homer, Moe, Lenny and Carl win the lottery, but Carl steals the ticket and leaves with the money for Iceland.
Episodes.title: The Saga of Carl

Episodes.description: When Marge tries to buy Homer snack cakes for their anniversary, she winds up meeting a married man who shares a common love of British television.
Episodes.title: Dangers on a Train
